                     <interp inst="t18231022-68-person648" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a harness-maker, and live in Marlborough-place, Great Peter-street. On the 12th of September, the prisoner sold me a horse collar for 1 s., and said he had an old chaise harness, which he had bought of Mr. Richardson, the lottery-office keeper's coachman, and would bring it next day, and on the 15th he brought it, and asked 25 s. for it - I agreed to give him 18 s., paid him 2 s. 6 d. in part, and on Wednesday paid him the rest.</p>
